<subSubSection pageNumber="490" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="490">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="490">Note:</emphasis>
Linnaeus included 
<taxonomicName authority="Turra (1765)" authorityName="Turra" authorityYear="1765" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosissimus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="490">Echinops spinosissimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation pageNumber="490" refId="references.r377">Turra (1765)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of his name and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="490">E. spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore illegitimate (see Greuter in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="490">Willdenowia</emphasis>
33: 58. 2003). However, both names appear to be in use for separate taxa (see e.g. Kozuharov in Tutin &amp; al., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="490">Fl. Europaea</emphasis>
4: 213. 1976).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
